review_blob:
I dont know. Maybe i got a bad bottle. It was skunked, most definitley light struck. It was a gift to my wife  from a friend for me, the brewer. But when i tasted this i just wasnt into it.

Popped the cap, no carbonation.  Poured it, no head.  Sourness, an unpleasant sweetness, followed by an unpleasant bitterness. probably wont be drinking this again, actually, i know i wont.

had a 2005 at my buddies house this last weekend. Its been 5 years this beer was aged... I must say it was quite delicious.  Very, very sharp carbonation that attacked the tongue and a raisin, malty taste.  The hop bitterness and qualities had faded over time, but it was still very good.
i actually really enjoyed this beer, one of the better porters i have had.  will definitley try again.
Terrible, maybe one of the grosser beers i have ever had. Tasted sour, or like a sock drug through the rocky  mountains.
beer_name: Avery The Kaiser Imperial Oktoberfest - Oak Barrel

review_blob: ick, was like drinking malt syrup.  I understand its supposed to be crazy, but i think a rating of 99%ile is a bit outrageous, but then again, how do you even classify this beast?
this was a good beer, surprised by its low rating, the blueberry taste was very noticeable.  I was burping up the flavor of blueberries all day
beer_name: Estes Park Bear Lake Blueberry Wheat

review_blob: This was flat out delicious.  Probalby one of the best beers on the market.  By far my favorite barley wine, hoppy, malty, strong, perfect blend.
This is a good brown, dry and smooth.  Good roasted flavor.  Probably one of the best browns ive ever had.
beer_name: AleSmith Nut Brown English-Style Ale (Bottle and Draft)

review_blob: Not as good as the other devil.  Its a good beer, but im just not enthralled with these "devil" brews.
This is ok, I wasnt to impressed with the devil series. They are good, but im just not that into belgians.
Good brew, malty, not as hoppy as thier other beers, also a bit fruity, I guess that can be expected with the belgian yeast.
God thats a good red ale.  Delicious, full in flavor, a bit dry.  Ale smith continues to impress.
Extremely hoppy, very delicious, full of flavor.  You can get these at a bunch of different breweries, fresh hops.
beer_name: Karl Strauss San Diego Brewers Guild Uncommon

review_blob: Very smooth on the pallette.  Dark brown, roasted malts and flavor.  Very easy to drink.Earlier Rating: 5/6/2007 Total Score: 4Very tasty, nice and smooth, the batch I had was not "to watery" but wasnt super thick either. I enjoyed this beer.
beer_name: Ballast Point Sextant Oatmeal Stout - Coffee 6.8% (2003-2013)

review_blob: This is a good beer, though it pales in comparison to their Sculpin IPA.  Very hoppy, citrusy taste, very well done.

This beer was very light and pretty clear for a heff.  Maybe it was just the certain bottle, but I must say, im not too impressed ... Weak aroma, very bland taste, this is budweiser with a slight banana flavor.
This was an ok beer, nothing spectacular.  A bit malty for my taste. It got better as it got warmer.
Weak aroma, taste, not so great, better than budweiser, but not by much...  I think it may be a tad bit overrated on this site.
Nice hop aroma, good biterness. This is a very balanced beer.  You can really taste the cascades throughout the sip. This is probably my favorite Sierra Nevada.
I really liked this beer. Good hop aroma, good hop taste, not to malty, bitter.  Cascades really come through.  I would love to drink this again.
ehh.  This was ok, kinda dry, Aroma lacking in the hops department, taste as well. I was not impressed.
This was a good beer. You can slightly taste the orange peel and the corriander comes through at the end. Very mild, a lot of yeast cake at the bottom.

A little to sweet for my taste, I prefer a hoppier Barley Wine.   This had a fruity taste, and the aroma was also very fruity.  I wasnt that impressed with this beer.  However, the ABV is well hidden.
beer_name: Flying Dog Horn Dog Barley Wine

review_blob: A little to sweet for my taste, I prefer a hoppier Barley Wine.   This had a fruity taste, and the aroma was also very fruity.  I wasnt that impressed with this beer.  However, the ABV is well hidden.
Another garbage beer. There is nothing "espcial" about this brew. Skunk, aluminum oxide taste, hops?  What hops?
Gross. Worse than regular corona.  Avoid.  There is nothing good about this beer. I dont know why everyone raves about corona.  Its garbage.
Ick, garbage, trash, horrible, one of the worst mexican beers I have ever had.  Tastes like metal.
Had this one in mexico.  Not a big fan of dos equis, but I guess if I had to choose, id pick DE over corona.  Typical mexican brew.
Good barley wine, highly hopped which adds to the character.  However I felt the alchohol was not as well hidden as say, the bigfoot barley wine.

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: This is a good brew. Tastes like your eating a liquid hop bush.  I would love to see the hopping schedule on this beer.  However, there is some malty character in there.  Delicious.

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: Like syrup, a brutally dark and coffee, imperial stoutish beer.  Good to drink nice and slow and savor the flavor, not a pounder, thats for sure.
THis is a great beer.  Very hoppy, very strong.  Nice dark color, one of my favorite beers from STONE.
beer_name: Stone Sublimely Self Righteous Black IPA

review_blob: Great Beer. Had the dry hopped vesion at a local pub. I recommend this ale to anyone.
beer_name: Rogue Dry Hopped St. Rogue Red Ale

review_blob: This was an ok stout, a little to sweet for me.  A lot of rasoted coffee flavors, some chocolate back there but not much.
beer_name: Anderson Valley Barney Flats Oatmeal Stout

review_blob: Good IPA, very basic, not to aggresive, although not too crazy either. Would definitley recommend it though.
I diddnt care for this hef.  Sour taste, lingering sour aftertaste.  Served to warm, wont try this one again.
Ok brew, strong hop flavor. Better than their original pale ale which i dont see on this board. This was their best beer I tasted.
Good stout, ther eis a roasted mocha flavor, some rasins.  Pretty think and not to dry. This was a good brew.
This is a good ale, very red in color, with a slight pepperiness in the nose.  Not much pepper in the taste, it seems to be used only for aromatic purposes. Some smokiness to it.
Darker, murkier appearance, stale hoppy aroma.  Sharp bitterness, not prolonged, but a very good taste.
MMM very good.  nice caramel flavor.  Lots of carbonation, reminds me of cookie dough. My favorite ESB.
THis is not so great. Its missing in aroma, and hoppy taste.  The hops are there, but not in a sufficient amount to satisfy a hop head like myself.  Im sticking with Ale Smith.
This is an interesting beer, much different than most stouts I have had.  This has a winey smell and flavor component, along with the roasted malts.  This is a very smooth beer.
Very nice porter, chocolate, mocha, very nice lingering after taste.  This also has a smokey flavor component to it as well.
This is an average Pale Ale.  I thought the water had a funny taste, almost stale.  Better than most, but could be more.

This was a good porter, one of my favorites.  This has a very strong coffee flavor, almost a little toffee as well. This is o ne of the only Kona beers I like. However, it was a little thin without the distinctive dry mouthfeel of most porters.
This is a good IPA, piny taste. Was definitley lacking in aroma when compared with some other IPAs. Very citrusy. Was cloudy in appearance.

Very nice taste, much different from a normal ale. Very dark, very malty, not much hops. The alcohol is hidden very well.  There is some brown sugar taste, it is very good and differnet from a normal ale.
Not a very good beer at all. Your much better sticking with AleSmith and Stone beers.  Malty, not very hoppy at all, did not enjoy the aftertaste.
EXCELLENT!  This was a very good and hoppy, bitter, alcohol was hidden very well, nice and drinkable.
